    <methods>
      <methodStep>
        <description>
          <para>A differential Global Positioning system was used to find the elevations of points in transects for this study. The repeatability of the system is approximately 5 cm. Points were measured in transects perpendicular to the stream. After measuring the elevation of a point the thaw depth was measure by pushing a thaw depth rod into the ground and measuring the depth of penetration. In some cases rocks were encountered before frozen ground was reached this was noted in the spreadsheet and no thaw depth was measured. In areas where the frozen ground was deeper the 125 cm the depth was noted as greater than 125cm.</para>
        </description>
      </methodStep>
    </methods>
